@layout Gsystem.Layout.SimpleLayout
<PageTitle>Section 5: Procedures for Disciplinary Action</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 5: Procedures for Disciplinary Action</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>5.1 Initial Response Procedures</h2>
            <p>When a disciplinary incident occurs, the following procedures shall be followed:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Immediate Response (Within 24 hours)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensure safety of all parties involved</li>
                    <li>Separate conflicting parties if necessary</li>
                    <li>Provide immediate medical attention if needed</li>
                    <li>Secure the scene and preserve evidence</li>
                    <li>Notify school administration immediately</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Documentation Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Complete incident report form</li>
                    <li>Record names of all witnesses</li>
                    <li>Take photographs if applicable</li>
                    <li>Obtain written statements from witnesses</li>
                    <li>Document any physical evidence</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.2 Investigation Process</h2>
            <p>The School Discipline Committee shall conduct a thorough investigation:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Investigation Timeline</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Day 1:</strong> Initial response and documentation</li>
                    <li><strong>Day 2-3:</strong> Witness interviews and evidence gathering</li>
                    <li><strong>Day 4-5:</strong> Committee review and deliberation</li>
                    <li><strong>Day 6-7:</strong> Decision making and notification</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Investigation Steps</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Interview the student(s) involved</li>
                    <li>Interview witnesses and staff members</li>
                    <li>Review relevant documentation</li>
                    <li>Consult with guidance counselor</li>
                    <li>Consider student's academic and behavioral history</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.3 Due Process Requirements</h2>
            <p>All disciplinary proceedings must ensure due process:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Student Rights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Right to be informed of charges</li>
                    <li>Right to present evidence and witnesses</li>
                    <li>Right to have parent/guardian present</li>
                    <li>Right to appeal decisions</li>
                    <li>Right to confidentiality</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Parent/Guardian Rights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Right to be notified of proceedings</li>
                    <li>Right to attend hearings</li>
                    <li>Right to review evidence</li>
                    <li>Right to appeal decisions</li>
                    <li>Right to request additional support services</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.4 Hearing Procedures</h2>
            <p>For serious violations, a formal hearing may be required:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Pre-Hearing Preparation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Notify all parties at least 48 hours in advance</li>
                    <li>Provide copies of all relevant documents</li>
                    <li>Arrange for appropriate accommodations</li>
                    <li>Ensure availability of support personnel</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Hearing Process</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Opening statements from all parties</li>
                    <li>Presentation of evidence and witnesses</li>
                    <li>Cross-examination of witnesses</li>
                    <li>Closing statements</li>
                    <li>Committee deliberation and decision</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.5 Decision Making Process</h2>
            <p>The committee shall make decisions based on:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Decision Criteria</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Severity and nature of the violation</li>
                    <li>Student's age and maturity level</li>
                    <li>Previous disciplinary history</li>
                    <li>Impact on school community</li>
                    <li>Potential for rehabilitation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Decision Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Majority vote of committee members</li>
                    <li>Written justification for decision</li>
                    <li>Specific disciplinary measures to be taken</li>
                    <li>Timeline for implementation</li>
                    <li>Follow-up monitoring plan</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.6 Notification and Implementation</h2>
            <p>Once a decision is made, the following steps shall be taken:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Notification Process</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Notify student and parents within 24 hours</li>
                    <li>Provide written decision with rationale</li>
                    <li>Explain appeal process and timeline</li>
                    <li>Schedule implementation meeting</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Implementation Steps</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Coordinate with relevant staff members</li>
                    <li>Implement disciplinary measures as decided</li>
                    <li>Monitor student progress and compliance</li>
                    <li>Provide necessary support services</li>
                    <li>Document all implementation activities</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5.7 Follow-up and Monitoring</h2>
            <p>After implementation, ongoing monitoring is essential:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Monitoring Activities</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Regular check-ins with student</li>
                    <li>Academic progress monitoring</li>
                    <li>Behavioral improvement tracking</li>
                    <li>Parent communication and updates</li>
                    <li>Teacher feedback and observations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Support Services</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Counseling and guidance services</li>
                    <li>Academic support and tutoring</li>
                    <li>Peer mentoring programs</li>
                    <li>Family counseling if needed</li>
                    <li>Community service opportunities</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

